Brief life is here our portion;
Brief sorrow, short-lived care;
The life that knows no ending,
The tearless life, is there.

Oh true Jerusalem, city most bright,
Whose perfect peace is eternal delight;
Longing in thee are fullfill'd, are express'd;
More than was long'd for embraced and possess.

Soon we'll reach the crystal river;
Soon our pilgrimage will cease;
Soon our golden harpstrings quiver,
With the melody of peace.

The saints of God! their conflict past,
And life's long battle won at last,
No more they need the shield or sword;
They cast them down before their Lord:
O happy saints! For ever blest;
At Jesus feet how safe their rest!.
